            , JUN. I am clerk to my father, whose name is Edward - he is a <rs id="t18290409-147-viclabel838" type="occupation">surveyor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290409-147-victim1445 t18290409-147-viclabel838"></join>. The prisoner was employed by us as a <rs id="t18290409-147-deflabel839" type="occupation">porter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290409-147-defend1443 t18290409-147-deflabel839"></join>, and to clean shoes; last Friday I hid myself in a closet in the office, from whence I could see where the money was kept, through a hole which I had made the day before; I saw the drawer open, and a hand put in and withdrawn again - I pushed the door open, and caught the prisoner with 3s. 6d. in his hand; he laid it down on the desk, and that money was missing from the drawer - he has been with us about eight months, and had 1l. per week.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-147-person1447">
